                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1268: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Trueblood</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-03T22:00:00-04:32"
                            >July 3, 1931—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>72. The departure of the Bolivian Minister at Asuncion for Buenos Aires is
                    scheduled for Sunday since he is unable to make travel connections until then.
                    The Minister for Foreign Affairs stated that his departure is irrevocable.
                    Argentine activity is continuing despite withdrawal of offer announced
                    definitely last night. I am informed regarding the Uruguayan proposal for a
                    military <hi rend="italic">status quo</hi> and international policing of the
                    Chaco.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Buenos Aires and Santiago.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Trueblood</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
